<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "What is a favicon and why is it important?", answer: "A favicon (favorite icon) is the small icon displayed in browser tabs, bookmarks, and address bars. It helps users identify your site among many open tabs and provides brand recognition. Favicons appear at 16x16 pixels in browser tabs, 32x32 in taskbars, and 180x180 as Apple touch icons. Missing favicons look unprofessional and make your site harder to find among open tabs." },
  { question: "What sizes do I need for a favicon?", answer: "Modern websites should provide at least four favicon sizes: 16x16 for browser tabs, 32x32 for taskbars and retina browser tabs, 48x48 for Windows shortcuts, and 180x180 for Apple touch icons (used when users add your site to their iOS home screen). Some sites also include a 192x192 icon for Android and a 512x512 for PWA splash screens." },
  { question: "What is the best format for favicons?", answer: "PNG is the recommended format for modern favicons because it supports transparency and is universally supported. The legacy ICO format can contain multiple sizes in a single file but is being phased out. SVG favicons are gaining support and offer perfect scaling at any size, but browser support is not yet universal. For maximum compatibility, use PNG for size-specific icons." },
  { question: "How do I add a favicon to my website?", answer: "Add link tags to the head section of your HTML. Use rel='icon' with type='image/png' and the sizes attribute for standard favicons. For Apple devices, use rel='apple-touch-icon' with sizes='180x180'. Place the actual PNG files in your site's root directory or adjust the href paths. This generator provides the exact HTML code you need." },
  { question: "Can I use text or initials as a favicon?", answer: "Yes, text-based favicons using one or two initials are a popular and effective approach, especially for personal brands, startups, or sites without a graphical logo. Choose a bold, readable font and ensure high contrast between the text and background color. At 16x16 pixels, simplicity is key -- single characters or two-letter initials work best." }
]) %>

